				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1621912#post-2465691</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1621912/the-lost-treasure-of-the-stranglefruits#post-2465691</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 01 Mar 2016 12:00:15 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Eta Carinae</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2110706</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Haaaaaaa. This feels SO good. Another piece from Daveyoufool I like!!!!!</p> <p>It took about two paragraphs, but then you definitely had me at <em>potassium cyanide didn't do his chronic asthma any favors</em>, and it only got better from there.</p> <p>Lil' typo:</p> <blockquote> <p>spouted a gravely throat</p> </blockquote> <p>I <em>suppose</em> it should be 'gravelly'. But then, you never know for sure with Dave&#8230;? ;&gt;</p> <p>I can only agree with I-don't-remember-who (sorry): we need more about the adventures of Dr. Spanko in search of SCP-2000. As for its adventures <span style="text-decoration: underline;">IN</span> SCP-2000&#8230; yes, that too, but something tells me they might be unpleasant? <span style="font-size:50%;">Is it a trap set by 05-12?</span></p> <p>Anyway, +1. And that's the way the cookie crumbles.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
